WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:13.790 align:middle line:90%


00:00:13.790 --> 00:00:16.830 align:middle line:90%
>> I am Ervin Laszlo.

00:00:16.830 --> 00:00:19.710 align:middle line:84%
And you asked me what I
have studied all my life.

00:00:19.710 --> 00:00:21.960 align:middle line:90%
I can say I've studied life.

00:00:21.960 --> 00:00:24.690 align:middle line:10%
I have not done any
formal studies at all,

00:00:24.690 --> 00:00:28.410 align:middle line:10%
not since I was in the
fifth grade, I think.

00:00:28.410 --> 00:00:30.570 align:middle line:10%
That was the last time
when the war intervened,

00:00:30.570 --> 00:00:31.860 align:middle line:10%
the Second World War.

00:00:31.860 --> 00:00:35.490 align:middle line:10%
And I launched a
career in music.

00:00:35.490 --> 00:00:39.150 align:middle line:84%
And sure, I studied it because
I was interested in everything

00:00:39.150 --> 00:00:42.570 align:middle line:84%
around me, interested in
finding out more things.

00:00:42.570 --> 00:00:44.380 align:middle line:90%
This is my chance.

00:00:44.380 --> 00:00:47.370 align:middle line:90%
And I had time and inclination.

00:00:47.370 --> 00:00:50.970 align:middle line:90%
So I have inquired.

00:00:50.970 --> 00:00:52.920 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't say
that I've studied.

00:00:52.920 --> 00:00:55.200 align:middle line:84%
I've not studied
anything for the sake

00:00:55.200 --> 00:00:58.110 align:middle line:84%
of studying for getting
a degree or getting

00:00:58.110 --> 00:01:00.310 align:middle line:90%
a diploma of some kind.

00:01:00.310 --> 00:01:02.190 align:middle line:90%
I did what I was interested in.

00:01:02.190 --> 00:01:04.440 align:middle line:84%
I was fortunate in my
life that I could live

00:01:04.440 --> 00:01:06.900 align:middle line:90%
like that as a concert pianist.

00:01:06.900 --> 00:01:09.690 align:middle line:84%
And later on when I started
writing and my books

00:01:09.690 --> 00:01:13.930 align:middle line:84%
got published, I was invited to
a university, Yale University

00:01:13.930 --> 00:01:17.650 align:middle line:84%
first, and then to New York
State University and others

00:01:17.650 --> 00:01:21.650 align:middle line:84%
without having actually
passed any degree, attended

00:01:21.650 --> 00:01:22.450 align:middle line:90%
a university.

00:01:22.450 --> 00:01:24.760 align:middle line:84%
I started teaching
on universities

00:01:24.760 --> 00:01:28.360 align:middle line:84%
without having attended
any university course.

00:01:28.360 --> 00:01:30.160 align:middle line:90%
So I could say yes.

00:01:30.160 --> 00:01:32.920 align:middle line:10%
I have studied who I am.

00:01:32.920 --> 00:01:35.770 align:middle line:10%
I've studied what the
world around me is.

00:01:35.770 --> 00:01:41.036 align:middle line:10%
But I have not studied a subject
for the sake of that subject.

00:01:41.036 --> 00:01:44.790 align:middle line:10%
>> You are known
for many things.

00:01:44.790 --> 00:01:49.950 align:middle line:84%
One is about the Akashic
records, the Akashic field.

00:01:49.950 --> 00:01:54.278 align:middle line:10%
And I would love for us to
be able to focus on that.

00:01:54.278 --> 00:01:58.050 align:middle line:84%
>> The Akashic field
is the universe.

00:01:58.050 --> 00:02:01.290 align:middle line:84%
It's how the universe
appears to us.

00:02:01.290 --> 00:02:04.710 align:middle line:84%
When we inquire how
things are connected,

00:02:04.710 --> 00:02:08.820 align:middle line:84%
how things are conserved,
we find the answer today

00:02:08.820 --> 00:02:10.289 align:middle line:90%
through the quantum sciences.

00:02:10.289 --> 00:02:13.570 align:middle line:84%
All things are connected
to all other things.

00:02:13.570 --> 00:02:17.500 align:middle line:84%
And nothing disappears
completely without a trace.

00:02:17.500 --> 00:02:20.100 align:middle line:84%
So the universe is
an Akashic field.

00:02:20.100 --> 00:02:22.410 align:middle line:84%
The ancients called
it an Akashic field.

00:02:22.410 --> 00:02:25.740 align:middle line:84%
Today, we can call it the
universe as it appears

00:02:25.740 --> 00:02:27.660 align:middle line:90%
in the quantum sciences.

00:02:27.660 --> 00:02:30.600 align:middle line:84%
It's an Akashic
universe, you might say.

00:02:30.600 --> 00:02:35.730 align:middle line:84%
And therefore, I have felt that
what I've been considering,

00:02:35.730 --> 00:02:40.110 align:middle line:84%
what I've been discussing so
many times, so many years is

00:02:40.110 --> 00:02:43.710 align:middle line:84%
actually-- is being
carried out, borne out

00:02:43.710 --> 00:02:46.060 align:middle line:84%
more and more in
the new sciences,

00:02:46.060 --> 00:02:49.980 align:middle line:84%
especially in quantum cosmology,
in quantum consciousness

00:02:49.980 --> 00:02:50.970 align:middle line:90%
research.

00:02:50.970 --> 00:02:55.260 align:middle line:84%
This is a remarkable
Akashic kind of a universe.

00:02:55.260 --> 00:02:58.390 align:middle line:84%
4,000, 5,000 years ago,
we would have called

00:02:58.390 --> 00:02:59.950 align:middle line:90%
it the Akashic dimension.

00:02:59.950 --> 00:03:01.840 align:middle line:90%
Today we call it reality.

00:03:01.840 --> 00:03:03.325 align:middle line:90%
But this is what it is.

00:03:03.325 --> 00:03:06.190 align:middle line:84%
>> Where did the word
Akashic come from?

00:03:06.190 --> 00:03:09.880 align:middle line:90%
>> The Akasha was the dimension.

00:03:09.880 --> 00:03:15.550 align:middle line:84%
The Hindu seers about 4
and 1/2, 5,000 years ago

00:03:15.550 --> 00:03:19.510 align:middle line:84%
talked about-- they said there
are four regular dimensions--

00:03:19.510 --> 00:03:21.820 align:middle line:90%
air, water, fire, and Earth.

00:03:21.820 --> 00:03:26.320 align:middle line:84%
And they called this
the standard dimension.

00:03:26.320 --> 00:03:29.350 align:middle line:84%
But they said there is a
higher or deeper dimension,

00:03:29.350 --> 00:03:32.630 align:middle line:84%
if you like, which
includes all the others.

00:03:32.630 --> 00:03:34.330 align:middle line:90%
This is beyond all the others.

00:03:34.330 --> 00:03:36.380 align:middle line:90%
It includes all the others.

00:03:36.380 --> 00:03:37.780 align:middle line:90%
It's the deep dimension.

00:03:37.780 --> 00:03:40.810 align:middle line:84%
Later on, Plato himself
talked about this

00:03:40.810 --> 00:03:45.940 align:middle line:84%
as a platonic
dimension of the soul,

00:03:45.940 --> 00:03:49.060 align:middle line:90%
of our consciousness, our mind.

00:03:49.060 --> 00:03:53.410 align:middle line:84%
But the Akashic dimension
or Akasha dimension

00:03:53.410 --> 00:03:57.325 align:middle line:84%
dates back probably
nearly 5,000 years.

00:03:57.325 --> 00:04:03.175 align:middle line:10%
>> Ervin, you were nominated for
a Nobel Prize at least twice.

00:04:03.175 --> 00:04:03.975 align:middle line:10%
Is that correct?

00:04:03.975 --> 00:04:05.250 align:middle line:10%
>> That is correct, yes.

00:04:05.250 --> 00:04:06.050 align:middle line:10%
>> OK.

00:04:06.050 --> 00:04:08.710 align:middle line:10%
What were you nominated for?

00:04:08.710 --> 00:04:15.400 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, my work in trying to
understand the relationships

00:04:15.400 --> 00:04:20.680 align:middle line:84%
that make our world what it is,
the systems, a world system,

00:04:20.680 --> 00:04:24.880 align:middle line:84%
a world system where all things
are interacting and dependent

00:04:24.880 --> 00:04:28.270 align:middle line:84%
on all other things, not
just the economy but also

00:04:28.270 --> 00:04:31.960 align:middle line:84%
the ecology, the culture,
as well as the finance.

00:04:31.960 --> 00:04:35.410 align:middle line:90%
And this is a systemic universe.

00:04:35.410 --> 00:04:40.840 align:middle line:84%
I developed the idea of a
universe, which is based

00:04:40.840 --> 00:04:43.030 align:middle line:90%
on the strong interconnections.

00:04:43.030 --> 00:04:47.920 align:middle line:84%
This is an Akashic
universe in a way.

00:04:47.920 --> 00:04:52.510 align:middle line:10%
Out of this modeling, if
you like, of the world

00:04:52.510 --> 00:04:55.630 align:middle line:10%
that we have created
on Earth came

00:04:55.630 --> 00:05:00.680 align:middle line:10%
a series of forecasts
and expectations,

00:05:00.680 --> 00:05:04.370 align:middle line:10%
provisions as to how
we could be evolving,

00:05:04.370 --> 00:05:06.200 align:middle line:10%
how we could be developing.

00:05:06.200 --> 00:05:09.590 align:middle line:84%
My main focus always
has been on development,

00:05:09.590 --> 00:05:12.830 align:middle line:84%
on evolution, not
just economic material

00:05:12.830 --> 00:05:16.550 align:middle line:84%
development but the development
of culture, of thought,

00:05:16.550 --> 00:05:18.420 align:middle line:90%
of spirit as well.

00:05:18.420 --> 00:05:23.120 align:middle line:84%
And so because I'm trying to
pull all these things together,

00:05:23.120 --> 00:05:26.420 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't fit into
any one discipline.

00:05:26.420 --> 00:05:29.270 align:middle line:84%
The Nobel Prizes are
set up by disciplines,

00:05:29.270 --> 00:05:33.770 align:middle line:84%
to the physics and biology
and other special disciplines.

00:05:33.770 --> 00:05:36.650 align:middle line:84%
At the time of Nobel,
there was no idea

00:05:36.650 --> 00:05:39.590 align:middle line:84%
that we could have a super
discipline, a kind of which

00:05:39.590 --> 00:05:42.810 align:middle line:84%
encompasses the others,
brings it together.

00:05:42.810 --> 00:05:46.700 align:middle line:84%
So this one then, I
was nominated then

00:05:46.700 --> 00:05:52.340 align:middle line:84%
for the Peace Prize because
this idea of an interconnected

00:05:52.340 --> 00:05:56.150 align:middle line:84%
universe of which we are a
part where we evolve together

00:05:56.150 --> 00:06:00.950 align:middle line:84%
with other things is a
universe of understanding,

00:06:00.950 --> 00:06:04.220 align:middle line:84%
coherence, and ultimately,
therefore, peace.

00:06:04.220 --> 00:06:09.390 align:middle line:84%
So indirectly without
addressing my work to peace

00:06:09.390 --> 00:06:12.680 align:middle line:84%
so specifically, I
created a foundation

00:06:12.680 --> 00:06:16.640 align:middle line:84%
for understanding the world
as a domain of coherence

00:06:16.640 --> 00:06:20.225 align:middle line:84%
where we can live
and evolve in peace.

00:06:20.225 --> 00:06:24.590 align:middle line:84%
>> That is your goal, is for
our world to live in peace.

00:06:24.590 --> 00:06:29.990 align:middle line:84%
I'm wondering, when it
comes to the Akashic field,

00:06:29.990 --> 00:06:34.230 align:middle line:84%
to the universe,
that somebody might

00:06:34.230 --> 00:06:36.940 align:middle line:90%
feel as though it's so huge.

00:06:36.940 --> 00:06:37.980 align:middle line:90%
It's so gargantuan.

00:06:37.980 --> 00:06:39.840 align:middle line:84%
Why would it be
important for them

00:06:39.840 --> 00:06:43.050 align:middle line:84%
to understand the
interconnectedness

00:06:43.050 --> 00:06:44.670 align:middle line:90%
of the universe?

00:06:44.670 --> 00:06:48.060 align:middle line:84%
>> Because we are
interconnected.

00:06:48.060 --> 00:06:51.090 align:middle line:90%
The universe is a hologram.

00:06:51.090 --> 00:06:53.910 align:middle line:84%
And in a hologram,
all the information

00:06:53.910 --> 00:06:57.450 align:middle line:84%
that generates the picture
is present in every part.

00:06:57.450 --> 00:07:01.320 align:middle line:84%
The universe may be
gargantuan, but it's in us.

00:07:01.320 --> 00:07:04.410 align:middle line:84%
Not only are we in the
universe, the universe

00:07:04.410 --> 00:07:08.850 align:middle line:84%
is in us because everything that
makes the universe what it is--

00:07:08.850 --> 00:07:11.220 align:middle line:84%
today we would call it
all the information,

00:07:11.220 --> 00:07:12.930 align:middle line:90%
all the energy flows--

00:07:12.930 --> 00:07:16.620 align:middle line:84%
is actually reflected in
every cell of our body,

00:07:16.620 --> 00:07:20.290 align:middle line:90%
in every atom in every cell.

00:07:20.290 --> 00:07:27.420 align:middle line:84%
So this is not a materialistic,
cold, independent universe

00:07:27.420 --> 00:07:29.220 align:middle line:90%
where all parts are separate.

00:07:29.220 --> 00:07:30.580 align:middle line:90%
Nothing is separate.

00:07:30.580 --> 00:07:33.090 align:middle line:84%
We are part of that
whole universe.

00:07:33.090 --> 00:07:35.260 align:middle line:84%
If you want to
understand ourselves,

00:07:35.260 --> 00:07:36.870 align:middle line:84%
we have to understand
the universe.

00:07:36.870 --> 00:07:38.970 align:middle line:84%
And we can't
understand the universe

00:07:38.970 --> 00:07:43.336 align:middle line:84%
until we have a better
understanding of ourselves.

00:07:43.336 --> 00:07:46.660 align:middle line:90%
>> Sounds like a catch-22.

00:07:46.660 --> 00:07:53.176 align:middle line:84%
What information, how do we know
that we are all interconnected?

00:07:53.176 --> 00:07:58.130 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, we have also experiments
on the levels of physics about

00:07:58.130 --> 00:08:00.710 align:middle line:84%
instant interconnection
beyond space and time.

00:08:00.710 --> 00:08:03.570 align:middle line:90%
It's called nonlocality.

00:08:03.570 --> 00:08:07.590 align:middle line:84%
And then we have obviously
the effects of what we do.

00:08:07.590 --> 00:08:09.750 align:middle line:84%
The great ecologist
Garrett Hardin

00:08:09.750 --> 00:08:14.130 align:middle line:84%
says you can't do just one thing
because you do any one thing,

00:08:14.130 --> 00:08:19.560 align:middle line:84%
it has a dozen or a million
consequences and side effects.

00:08:19.560 --> 00:08:22.200 align:middle line:84%
We are connected
because everything we do

00:08:22.200 --> 00:08:24.960 align:middle line:90%
is linked to everything else.

00:08:24.960 --> 00:08:27.210 align:middle line:90%
It's like being in a network.

00:08:27.210 --> 00:08:31.590 align:middle line:84%
When you're in a network, all
the participants in a network

00:08:31.590 --> 00:08:34.919 align:middle line:84%
hear, know, perceive
what you're doing.

00:08:34.919 --> 00:08:36.549 align:middle line:90%
And they respond.

00:08:36.549 --> 00:08:38.679 align:middle line:84%
And that is the nature
of the universe.

00:08:38.679 --> 00:08:41.440 align:middle line:84%
It's a coherent-- it's
a single universe.

00:08:41.440 --> 00:08:42.840 align:middle line:90%
It's a one universe.

00:08:42.840 --> 00:08:45.660 align:middle line:84%
The great physicist
Erwin Schrödinger

00:08:45.660 --> 00:08:49.720 align:middle line:84%
said there is no such thing as
consciousness in the plural.

00:08:49.720 --> 00:08:51.000 align:middle line:90%
Now, what did he mean by that?

00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:53.760 align:middle line:84%
He said there is no such
thing as my consciousness

00:08:53.760 --> 00:08:55.290 align:middle line:90%
and your consciousness.

00:08:55.290 --> 00:08:58.930 align:middle line:84%
It's only our consciousness,
the one consciousness

00:08:58.930 --> 00:09:01.650 align:middle line:84%
which pervades the universe
because the universe has

00:09:01.650 --> 00:09:06.090 align:middle line:84%
an aspect, which is mind-like,
not just physical-like, not

00:09:06.090 --> 00:09:07.440 align:middle line:90%
just matter-like.

00:09:07.440 --> 00:09:10.920 align:middle line:84%
There is no longer a separation
between mind and matter.

00:09:10.920 --> 00:09:14.110 align:middle line:84%
Nothing is beyond
any other thing.

00:09:14.110 --> 00:09:17.520 align:middle line:84%
So it's an entirely
new way of thinking.

00:09:17.520 --> 00:09:22.640 align:middle line:84%
It's also a very old way because
the great thinkers of antiquity,

00:09:22.640 --> 00:09:27.280 align:middle line:84%
the Buddhists, for example,
the Taoists knew this.

00:09:27.280 --> 00:09:31.750 align:middle line:84%
And they considered the universe
as an interconnected whole,

00:09:31.750 --> 00:09:35.080 align:middle line:84%
which is suffused
by a higher spirit.

00:09:35.080 --> 00:09:38.560 align:middle line:84%
In modern science, in
contemporary science,

00:09:38.560 --> 00:09:43.670 align:middle line:84%
we talk about an interconnected
dynamic attractors

00:09:43.670 --> 00:09:48.280 align:middle line:84%
are dynamic impulses which are
present in the universe, which

00:09:48.280 --> 00:09:51.460 align:middle line:84%
is present in us,
in each one of us.

00:09:51.460 --> 00:09:55.090 align:middle line:84%
We reflect the universe
because we are connected to it,

00:09:55.090 --> 00:09:56.140 align:middle line:90%
we are part of it.

00:09:56.140 --> 00:10:00.520 align:middle line:84%
These concepts are so basic,
so large that you can't simply

00:10:00.520 --> 00:10:05.350 align:middle line:84%
deduct them, reduce them, or
derive them from something else.

00:10:05.350 --> 00:10:06.700 align:middle line:90%
They are fundamental.

00:10:06.700 --> 00:10:08.110 align:middle line:90%
This is how we start.

00:10:08.110 --> 00:10:10.570 align:middle line:84%
It's not how we come
to this conclusion

00:10:10.570 --> 00:10:12.010 align:middle line:90%
from looking at something else.

00:10:12.010 --> 00:10:14.410 align:middle line:84%
This something
else is also this.

00:10:14.410 --> 00:10:17.680 align:middle line:84%
Schrodinger says, you can't
go beyond consciousness.

00:10:17.680 --> 00:10:20.200 align:middle line:90%
And consciousness is one.

00:10:20.200 --> 00:10:23.200 align:middle line:84%
So what we start
with and what we have

00:10:23.200 --> 00:10:26.830 align:middle line:84%
is the sense that
we are a being who

00:10:26.830 --> 00:10:31.180 align:middle line:84%
is emerged in space and time,
who is evolving in space

00:10:31.180 --> 00:10:33.820 align:middle line:84%
and time, and who
is interconnecting

00:10:33.820 --> 00:10:38.995 align:middle line:84%
with all other things that
evolve in space and time.

00:10:38.995 --> 00:10:44.950 align:middle line:84%
>> Ervin, is it true that
humans create a past, a present,

00:10:44.950 --> 00:10:48.490 align:middle line:84%
and a future and that really
time is just there is no time

00:10:48.490 --> 00:10:50.110 align:middle line:90%
that we know.

00:10:50.110 --> 00:10:53.950 align:middle line:84%
So to that end, does that
mean that the information

00:10:53.950 --> 00:10:58.180 align:middle line:84%
for our future or
definitely our past

00:10:58.180 --> 00:11:01.810 align:middle line:84%
is somewhere as if it's
a big gigantic library?

00:11:01.810 --> 00:11:03.700 align:middle line:90%
>> It is.

00:11:03.700 --> 00:11:07.350 align:middle line:84%
It's the Akashic
records, if you like.

00:11:07.350 --> 00:11:13.270 align:middle line:84%
Information cannot be
created and cannot be deleted

00:11:13.270 --> 00:11:18.080 align:middle line:84%
because this is a world which
is an interconnected field.

00:11:18.080 --> 00:11:19.690 align:middle line:84%
That's why I call
it the Akashic field

00:11:19.690 --> 00:11:24.400 align:middle line:84%
because the Akashic records
are maintained in this field.

00:11:24.400 --> 00:11:28.700 align:middle line:84%
This field is an energy
and information field.

00:11:28.700 --> 00:11:33.250 align:middle line:84%
It's a quantum field and
strongly interconnected.

00:11:33.250 --> 00:11:35.980 align:middle line:84%
Reflecting one thing
reflects another.

00:11:35.980 --> 00:11:39.220 align:middle line:84%
Things don't just push
and pull each other.

00:11:39.220 --> 00:11:41.650 align:middle line:90%
They resonate with each other.

00:11:41.650 --> 00:11:43.210 align:middle line:90%
They show up again.

00:11:43.210 --> 00:11:46.540 align:middle line:84%
There is such a thing as
information created here

00:11:46.540 --> 00:11:48.370 align:middle line:90%
having an effect over there.

00:11:48.370 --> 00:11:53.560 align:middle line:84%
And over there could be another
planet, could be another galaxy.

00:11:53.560 --> 00:11:58.570 align:middle line:84%
As far as we know, this universe
is a single resonated field

00:11:58.570 --> 00:12:02.290 align:middle line:84%
in which all things are
connected with all other things.

00:12:02.290 --> 00:12:04.240 align:middle line:90%
This is a basic concept.

00:12:04.240 --> 00:12:07.000 align:middle line:84%
It's a basic concept that
has been known, as I said,

00:12:07.000 --> 00:12:08.620 align:middle line:90%
to the ancient thinkers.

00:12:08.620 --> 00:12:10.810 align:middle line:90%
It's re-emerging today.

00:12:10.810 --> 00:12:13.730 align:middle line:84%
And it gives us an
entirely different view

00:12:13.730 --> 00:12:17.810 align:middle line:84%
from the standard classical view
of a material universe where

00:12:17.810 --> 00:12:19.880 align:middle line:84%
bits and pieces
of matter are just

00:12:19.880 --> 00:12:23.300 align:middle line:84%
moving about in passive
space and in different time.

00:12:23.300 --> 00:12:25.340 align:middle line:90%
That's the Newtonian paradigm.

00:12:25.340 --> 00:12:29.240 align:middle line:84%
And that has led to this
machine concept of the universe

00:12:29.240 --> 00:12:31.880 align:middle line:84%
where everything is
separate, everything

00:12:31.880 --> 00:12:35.870 align:middle line:84%
can be treated individually,
where things can be broken apart

00:12:35.870 --> 00:12:38.120 align:middle line:84%
and perhaps can
be rebuilt again.

00:12:38.120 --> 00:12:40.640 align:middle line:84%
But everything is
basically separate.

00:12:40.640 --> 00:12:44.220 align:middle line:84%
Einstein said that this
separation is an illusion.

00:12:44.220 --> 00:12:46.130 align:middle line:84%
And I think all the
great physicists,

00:12:46.130 --> 00:12:48.440 align:middle line:84%
the great scientists
today concur

00:12:48.440 --> 00:12:51.410 align:middle line:90%
there is no absolute separation.

00:12:51.410 --> 00:12:54.020 align:middle line:84%
I am not here and
you over there.

00:12:54.020 --> 00:12:57.230 align:middle line:84%
We share the same space
and the same time.

00:12:57.230 --> 00:13:00.530 align:middle line:84%
And our destiny is
also interlinked.

00:13:00.530 --> 00:13:03.260 align:middle line:84%
I believe that everything
that ever happened

00:13:03.260 --> 00:13:06.920 align:middle line:84%
is here to influence
what is happening now.

00:13:06.920 --> 00:13:09.920 align:middle line:84%
I don't believe that
it determines what is

00:13:09.920 --> 00:13:11.610 align:middle line:90%
going to happen in the future.

00:13:11.610 --> 00:13:14.900 align:middle line:84%
I think this universe
has a degree of freedom.

00:13:14.900 --> 00:13:16.880 align:middle line:90%
Things can be created.

00:13:16.880 --> 00:13:18.780 align:middle line:90%
Things can evolve.

00:13:18.780 --> 00:13:21.360 align:middle line:90%
Things can be decided yet.

00:13:21.360 --> 00:13:25.610 align:middle line:84%
In fact, we're living through
an epoch now after the--

00:13:25.610 --> 00:13:29.660 align:middle line:84%
we're still in the pandemic but
certainly after a big crisis

00:13:29.660 --> 00:13:32.600 align:middle line:84%
in which many things
become possible.

00:13:32.600 --> 00:13:37.170 align:middle line:84%
But these many things are
not prescribed in the past.

00:13:37.170 --> 00:13:41.690 align:middle line:84%
We can create the future, not
without limits, of course.

00:13:41.690 --> 00:13:44.430 align:middle line:84%
It has to be built on what
has already been there.

00:13:44.430 --> 00:13:47.820 align:middle line:84%
But the past does not
determine the future.

00:13:47.820 --> 00:13:51.800 align:middle line:84%
The future is determined by
how we interact in the present.

00:13:51.800 --> 00:13:54.090 align:middle line:90%
Together, all of us--

00:13:54.090 --> 00:13:57.500 align:middle line:84%
that means all beings
in space and time--

00:13:57.500 --> 00:14:02.576 align:middle line:84%
through their interaction create
the world that is coming to be.

00:14:02.576 --> 00:14:06.510 align:middle line:84%
>> Ervin, how do you think it
came to be that we decided we

00:14:06.510 --> 00:14:08.926 align:middle line:90%
were separate from one another?

00:14:08.926 --> 00:14:10.680 align:middle line:90%
>> It's convenient.

00:14:10.680 --> 00:14:12.910 align:middle line:84%
It's very convenient
to take things apart,

00:14:12.910 --> 00:14:14.580 align:middle line:90%
and then you can manipulate it.

00:14:14.580 --> 00:14:15.840 align:middle line:90%
You build a bicycle.

00:14:15.840 --> 00:14:18.670 align:middle line:84%
And if the pedal doesn't
work, you change the pedal.

00:14:18.670 --> 00:14:19.470 align:middle line:90%
You see?

00:14:19.470 --> 00:14:21.450 align:middle line:90%
Or the spokes on the wheel.

00:14:21.450 --> 00:14:23.020 align:middle line:90%
It's very convenient.

00:14:23.020 --> 00:14:25.020 align:middle line:84%
You can take things
apart, fix it,

00:14:25.020 --> 00:14:26.340 align:middle line:90%
and put it back together again.

00:14:26.340 --> 00:14:28.020 align:middle line:90%
That's the ideal.

00:14:28.020 --> 00:14:32.260 align:middle line:84%
In nature also, we can take
what we want from nature,

00:14:32.260 --> 00:14:36.960 align:middle line:84%
then we can manipulate things
and replace it somehow.

00:14:36.960 --> 00:14:38.400 align:middle line:90%
But it's all separate.

00:14:38.400 --> 00:14:41.890 align:middle line:84%
It all can be
independently handled.

00:14:41.890 --> 00:14:45.350 align:middle line:84%
Technology is based on
that, materials technology,

00:14:45.350 --> 00:14:49.030 align:middle line:84%
not the new technology, not
the electronic technology.

00:14:49.030 --> 00:14:51.940 align:middle line:84%
The way we are registered
in this conversation

00:14:51.940 --> 00:14:53.860 align:middle line:84%
that we have across
the continents

00:14:53.860 --> 00:14:56.630 align:middle line:90%
is not a material phenomenon.

00:14:56.630 --> 00:15:00.070 align:middle line:84%
It's not a little bits of matter
being moved here and there.

00:15:00.070 --> 00:15:04.720 align:middle line:84%
It's information being
cycled simultaneously.

00:15:04.720 --> 00:15:09.160 align:middle line:84%
And in reality, it's
even cycled even more

00:15:09.160 --> 00:15:13.930 align:middle line:84%
because we in our deeper
sense with our consciousness,

00:15:13.930 --> 00:15:16.960 align:middle line:84%
we can perceive others
in a deeper sense.

00:15:16.960 --> 00:15:18.880 align:middle line:84%
And the great yogis
have known this.

00:15:18.880 --> 00:15:21.190 align:middle line:84%
The great spiritual
masters have known this.

00:15:21.190 --> 00:15:25.570 align:middle line:84%
And now this experiment for the
nonlocality of consciousness,

00:15:25.570 --> 00:15:30.010 align:middle line:84%
for distance remote
perceptions, remote healing,

00:15:30.010 --> 00:15:32.125 align:middle line:84%
there is new evidence
for all of this.

00:15:32.125 --> 00:15:34.360 align:middle line:84%
This is very, very
different from

00:15:34.360 --> 00:15:37.660 align:middle line:84%
the separate
materialistic world which

00:15:37.660 --> 00:15:40.060 align:middle line:84%
our fathers and forefathers
thought they had.

00:15:40.060 --> 00:15:42.520 align:middle line:84%
And because they
created technologies,

00:15:42.520 --> 00:15:46.720 align:middle line:84%
they created a world based on
that materialist, separatist

00:15:46.720 --> 00:15:50.320 align:middle line:84%
idea, they could
destroy the harmony.

00:15:50.320 --> 00:15:53.620 align:middle line:84%
They could destroy the oneness,
which otherwise would be there

00:15:53.620 --> 00:15:54.760 align:middle line:90%
in nature.

00:15:54.760 --> 00:15:57.880 align:middle line:84%
So that was a dangerous
way to proceed.

00:15:57.880 --> 00:15:59.200 align:middle line:90%
We are learning it.

00:15:59.200 --> 00:16:01.780 align:middle line:84%
And we are also paying
the cost of what

00:16:01.780 --> 00:16:05.660 align:middle line:84%
it is when you break apart
the resonance, the wholeness

00:16:05.660 --> 00:16:07.040 align:middle line:90%
of the world in which we live.

00:16:07.040 --> 00:16:09.060 align:middle line:84%
And we just look at
one thing at a time,

00:16:09.060 --> 00:16:11.870 align:middle line:84%
us seeing our nation,
our country first,

00:16:11.870 --> 00:16:13.160 align:middle line:90%
never mind the rest.

00:16:13.160 --> 00:16:15.980 align:middle line:84%
That kind of
thinking takes apart

00:16:15.980 --> 00:16:18.050 align:middle line:90%
the coherence of the whole.

00:16:18.050 --> 00:16:23.060 align:middle line:84%
And it breaks apart
the very basis of life.

00:16:23.060 --> 00:16:24.590 align:middle line:90%
Let me just add.

00:16:24.590 --> 00:16:30.140 align:middle line:10%
Life is only possible if
every quantum, every particle

00:16:30.140 --> 00:16:33.170 align:middle line:10%
in every cell of
our body cooperates

00:16:33.170 --> 00:16:34.970 align:middle line:10%
with every other cell.

00:16:34.970 --> 00:16:38.240 align:middle line:84%
If there is a break in
cooperation anywhere,

00:16:38.240 --> 00:16:40.080 align:middle line:90%
it's a disease.

00:16:40.080 --> 00:16:42.060 align:middle line:84%
If there is a break
in cooperation

00:16:42.060 --> 00:16:45.780 align:middle line:84%
and their subsidiary elements
of cooperation come together,

00:16:45.780 --> 00:16:46.830 align:middle line:90%
that's a disease.

00:16:46.830 --> 00:16:48.090 align:middle line:90%
That's a serious disease.

00:16:48.090 --> 00:16:49.950 align:middle line:90%
That's cancer.

00:16:49.950 --> 00:16:55.650 align:middle line:84%
And eventually, that separate
development of growth

00:16:55.650 --> 00:16:58.320 align:middle line:90%
is killing the host, as we know.

00:16:58.320 --> 00:17:04.089 align:middle line:84%
So just in this whole body
is a cooperative system,

00:17:04.089 --> 00:17:09.839 align:middle line:84%
so is the whole human world, the
whole world in the biosphere,

00:17:09.839 --> 00:17:11.490 align:middle line:90%
a cooperative system.

00:17:11.490 --> 00:17:13.980 align:middle line:90%
We have neglected it.

00:17:13.980 --> 00:17:15.300 align:middle line:90%
We have forgotten it.

00:17:15.300 --> 00:17:16.740 align:middle line:90%
We have ignored it.

00:17:16.740 --> 00:17:18.430 align:middle line:90%
And we are paying the price.

00:17:18.430 --> 00:17:20.040 align:middle line:90%
We are now coming back to it.

00:17:20.040 --> 00:17:23.730 align:middle line:84%
It takes sometimes a crisis
to make us see the light,

00:17:23.730 --> 00:17:25.210 align:middle line:90%
to make us see which way to go.

00:17:25.210 --> 00:17:26.460 align:middle line:90%
Now we are learning.

00:17:26.460 --> 00:17:29.190 align:middle line:84%
I think we have learned
just now that we

00:17:29.190 --> 00:17:30.760 align:middle line:90%
are all in the same boat.

00:17:30.760 --> 00:17:35.070 align:middle line:84%
What happens any one part has an
influence on every other part,

00:17:35.070 --> 00:17:38.040 align:middle line:84%
and that together,
we have the option,

00:17:38.040 --> 00:17:40.680 align:middle line:84%
option not only to
mechanically go on

00:17:40.680 --> 00:17:43.350 align:middle line:84%
and doing the same thing as
we have always been doing

00:17:43.350 --> 00:17:46.350 align:middle line:84%
but to do something,
what we really want

00:17:46.350 --> 00:17:50.100 align:middle line:84%
because this is a
permissible universe.

00:17:50.100 --> 00:17:52.260 align:middle line:84%
A permissive universe
in that sense,

00:17:52.260 --> 00:17:54.660 align:middle line:90%
it allows many things to happen.

00:17:54.660 --> 00:17:57.420 align:middle line:84%
We are not forced
into a cage, not

00:17:57.420 --> 00:18:01.140 align:middle line:84%
forced into a big wheel where
we can only do one thing.

00:18:01.140 --> 00:18:03.240 align:middle line:84%
That's a lesson we
are now learning.

00:18:03.240 --> 00:18:06.510 align:middle line:84%
And we have to make use of it
because we cannot just keep

00:18:06.510 --> 00:18:08.310 align:middle line:84%
going doing what
we have been doing.

00:18:08.310 --> 00:18:10.870 align:middle line:84%
That's what leads to
more and more breakdowns.

00:18:10.870 --> 00:18:13.560 align:middle line:84%
We have to go forward
and create a world

00:18:13.560 --> 00:18:16.680 align:middle line:84%
where all people interact,
where all people can live,

00:18:16.680 --> 00:18:18.580 align:middle line:90%
all people can flourish.

00:18:18.580 --> 00:18:20.370 align:middle line:90%
We can do it.

00:18:20.370 --> 00:18:21.720 align:middle line:90%
The information is there.

00:18:21.720 --> 00:18:25.200 align:middle line:84%
Our technologies properly
used, properly developed

00:18:25.200 --> 00:18:26.670 align:middle line:90%
can serve this.

00:18:26.670 --> 00:18:28.210 align:middle line:90%
It's up to us.

00:18:28.210 --> 00:18:30.520 align:middle line:84%
So I think it's a
tremendous opportunity.

00:18:30.520 --> 00:18:32.890 align:middle line:90%
It's an exciting time to live.

00:18:32.890 --> 00:18:36.020 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't exchange it for
any other time in history.

00:18:36.020 --> 00:18:39.140 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, that's
saying a lot, Ervin.

00:18:39.140 --> 00:18:43.670 align:middle line:84%
There is things that seem to get
in the way of being able to have

00:18:43.670 --> 00:18:45.950 align:middle line:84%
the kind of peace
that you talk about,

00:18:45.950 --> 00:18:50.780 align:middle line:84%
egos and all of the things
that come with that.

00:18:50.780 --> 00:18:54.290 align:middle line:84%
Do you think it's even
possible for humans

00:18:54.290 --> 00:18:56.730 align:middle line:90%
to have this kind of peace?

00:18:56.730 --> 00:18:59.940 align:middle line:84%
>> Nature has that
kind of a peace.

00:18:59.940 --> 00:19:03.170 align:middle line:84%
I live here in a
hilltop in Tuscany.

00:19:03.170 --> 00:19:05.120 align:middle line:90%
And I see nature around me.

00:19:05.120 --> 00:19:06.500 align:middle line:90%
Nature is whole.

00:19:06.500 --> 00:19:08.330 align:middle line:90%
Nature is harmonious.

00:19:08.330 --> 00:19:10.910 align:middle line:84%
It's we who created
this harmony,

00:19:10.910 --> 00:19:13.070 align:middle line:84%
so it's not something
we have to create.

00:19:13.070 --> 00:19:16.250 align:middle line:84%
It's something we
have to eliminate,

00:19:16.250 --> 00:19:17.990 align:middle line:90%
eliminate the disturbance.

00:19:17.990 --> 00:19:21.050 align:middle line:84%
We have become a
noise in the system.

00:19:21.050 --> 00:19:25.290 align:middle line:84%
We have got to get rid of this,
go back to what we truly are.

00:19:25.290 --> 00:19:27.920 align:middle line:90%
We are part of a whole system.

00:19:27.920 --> 00:19:31.280 align:middle line:84%
We are a whole
harmonious resonant part.

00:19:31.280 --> 00:19:35.690 align:middle line:84%
We have got to learn to act
like we are what we truly are.

00:19:35.690 --> 00:19:38.540 align:middle line:84%
We are healthy
when we are whole.

00:19:38.540 --> 00:19:41.430 align:middle line:84%
And very interestingly
enough, in several languages

00:19:41.430 --> 00:19:44.580 align:middle line:84%
that I know, even the
very concept of health

00:19:44.580 --> 00:19:46.980 align:middle line:90%
means wholeness.

00:19:46.980 --> 00:19:49.410 align:middle line:90%
And this is true.

00:19:49.410 --> 00:19:51.760 align:middle line:90%
And the ancients knew it.

00:19:51.760 --> 00:19:55.180 align:middle line:84%
I've been looking at some
ancient scriptures, for example,

00:19:55.180 --> 00:19:56.310 align:middle line:90%
about health.

00:19:56.310 --> 00:19:59.730 align:middle line:84%
And they all say, the
person who is well adjusted,

00:19:59.730 --> 00:20:03.090 align:middle line:84%
the person who has moral
virtues, the person who

00:20:03.090 --> 00:20:06.150 align:middle line:84%
can live together in
peace with others, that's

00:20:06.150 --> 00:20:08.400 align:middle line:90%
the person who is healthy.

00:20:08.400 --> 00:20:12.960 align:middle line:84%
And they've told this to
us thousands of years ago.

00:20:12.960 --> 00:20:15.210 align:middle line:84%
We just thought we
can make ourselves

00:20:15.210 --> 00:20:19.260 align:middle line:84%
healthy by mechanical,
biochemical, biophysical means.

00:20:19.260 --> 00:20:21.270 align:middle line:84%
That can help, of
course, sometimes

00:20:21.270 --> 00:20:22.980 align:middle line:90%
if there is a disease at hand.

00:20:22.980 --> 00:20:27.300 align:middle line:84%
But the way to be
healthy is to be one,

00:20:27.300 --> 00:20:31.770 align:middle line:84%
to respect your oneness within
your body and your oneness

00:20:31.770 --> 00:20:33.360 align:middle line:90%
with the world around you.

00:20:33.360 --> 00:20:34.620 align:middle line:90%
That's healthy.

00:20:34.620 --> 00:20:36.460 align:middle line:90%
That's flourishing.

00:20:36.460 --> 00:20:38.690 align:middle line:90%
That's peace.

00:20:38.690 --> 00:20:45.260 align:middle line:84%
Peace, health, oneness
are all the same concept.

00:20:45.260 --> 00:20:50.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Back up a little bit, Ervin,
you mentioned very quickly that

00:20:50.660 --> 00:20:55.830 align:middle line:84%
you had a second chance studying
the way that you did, reading,

00:20:55.830 --> 00:20:56.630 align:middle line:90%
